class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfFour(int n) {
        if (n <= 0) {
            return false;
        }
        while (n % 4 == 0) {
            n /= 4;
        }
        return n == 1;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution repeatedly divides the input by 4 until it's no longer divisible. If the final result is 1, it's a power of four. This approach leverages the fact that a power of four can be expressed as a product of 4s.

